Title: Column: Can Brexit be used by businesses to abandon leases?
Summary: We have endured many debates about the potential political and economic consequences of Brexit. What has, until now, received less attention is the fact that it may also have far reaching legal consequences. In one of the most recent examples of the burning nature of the issue, the European Medicines Agency (EMA) is arguing that Brexit amounts to an unforeseen event of “frustration” of its 25 year lease. Partner Philip Sewell and Associate Sarah Walker in the commercial disputes and regulation team at law firm Shepherd & Wedderburn explore.
